The `event_study()` function provides a common API for several event study estimators.

::: {#ddfc5310 .cell execution_count=51}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit_twfe = pf.event_study(
    data=df_het,
    yname="dep_var",
    idname="state",
    tname="year",
    gname="g",
    estimator="twfe",
)

fit_did2s = pf.event_study(
    data=df_het,
    yname="dep_var",
    idname="state",
    tname="year",
    gname="g",
    estimator="did2s",
)

pf.etable([fit_twfe, fit_did2s])
